<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="95" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d95">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4787</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Sofia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MDI1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-10T22:00:00+02:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 10, 1917, 10 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 19, 3.35
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Audience with Minister for Foreign Affairs Wednesday. Received
                                assurances that there would be no break in relations happily
                                existing between the two countries. German-Austrian pressure is
                                still very great but up to date has failed. Official circles in
                                Bulgaria strongly in favor of friendly relations, public sentiment
                                likewise. Newspaper reports of disturbances in Bulgaria entirely
                                unfounded.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MDI1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>